SONGBIRD Lira is once again taking fans on a journey into her heart.&nbsp;Lira&rsquo;s reality show, Dreamchaser: Born Free, hits the screens for a second season on Wednesday.The show gives viewers an insight into Lira&rsquo;s production, songwriting processes and all her tours.The soulful singer said she had no problem inviting fans into her creative space.&ldquo;My fans will better understand my inner-world. And I cherish that honour.&ldquo;I&rsquo;m overly excited to share my story with viewers &ndash; my joys, challenges, effort, experiences as well as chasing my dream,&rdquo; she said.The show documents the making of her new album, Born Free.The Daveyton, Ekurhuleni-born star said there&rsquo;s a lot to learn from her experiences.&ldquo;Inspiration, dedication, love, heartache, victory and accomplishment are some of the things I hope my fans will learn from the show.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a personal reflection of my journey, and what it takes to be in this crazy industry.&rdquo;The award-winning musician said the idea to take fans on her journey came from recordings by her husband, Robin Kohl.&ldquo;He&rsquo;s been filming me and my band&rsquo;s performances for many years, including our on-the-road experiences and studio sessions.&ldquo;On a visit to Dubai, he edited a short promo, and we asked: &lsquo;Can this be turned into something?&rsquo;.&ldquo;Dreamchaser was born during our first tour to the US.&rdquo;Catch Mzansi&rsquo;s songstress Lira in Dreamchaser: Born Free to be aired on Fox Life (DStv channel 126) on Wednesday at 8pm.&nbsp;